SIMPLE: flagellum
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flagellum
<hw>Fla*gel"lum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
E. <plw>Flagellums</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, L. <plw>Flagella</plw>
<pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., a whip. See <er>Flagellate</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A young, flexible
shoot of a plant; esp., the long trailing branch of a vine, or a slender
branch in certain mosses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A long, whiplike
cilium. See <er>Flagellata</er>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>An appendage of
the reproductive apparatus of the snail.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>A
lashlike appendage of a crustacean, esp. the terminal portion of the
antenn⟦ae⟧ and the epipodite of the maxilipeds. See
<er>Maxilliped</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 566 --></p>

<p><ent>Flageolet</ent>⟦br⟧
